comment.body:
Based on what I get from Alma's writings: 

in the short term, economic data and (geo)political risks are there; 

in the medium to long term, obviously the market, especially tech, is already frothy; two scenarios are: 1. if Fed cuts, then the bubble will be further inflated until a major burst in the longer time horizon, 2. if not cut, then correction in the form of more organized sell, which also aims to put Trump's midterm in trouble.

